# Verify after edits

After creating or changing files under `frontend/`, run checks **on the affected paths** (avoid scanning the whole project when unnecessary).

## Commands (from `frontend/`)

```bash
# Format (JS/TS/Astro/CSS/SCSS/JSON)
pnpm exec prettier --write --ignore-unknown "path/to/changed/**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,astro,css,scss,json}"

# JS/TS/Astro
pnpm exec eslint "path/to/changed/**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,astro}"

# SCSS/CSS/Astro
pnpm exec stylelint "path/to/changed/**/*.{scss,css,astro}"

# TypeScript
pnpm tsc
```

For a single file, pass the exact path, e.g. `src/shared/ui/RoundButton/RoundButton.astro`.

## Order

1. Make the changes.
2. Run `prettier --write` on the changed files or folder.
3. Run `eslint` and `stylelint` on the changed files or folder.
4. Run `pnpm tsc` (whole project — types are cross-module).
5. Fix errors before replying to the user.
